content.text: How Can XML be Used?
XML is used in many aspects of web development.
content.html: XML is used in many aspects of web development.

content.text: XML is often used to separate data from presentation.
content.html: XML is often used to separate data from presentation.

content.text: XML Separates Data from Presentation
XML does not carry any information about how to be displayed.
content.html: XML does not carry any information about how to be displayed.

content.text: The same XML data can be used in many different presentation scenarios.
content.html: The same XML data can be used in many different presentation scenarios.

content.text: Because of this, with XML, there is a full separation between data and presentation.
content.html: Because of this, with XML, there is a full separation between data and presentation.

content.text: XML is Often a Complement to HTML
In many HTML applications, XML is used to store or transport data, while HTML is used to format and display the same data.
content.html: In many HTML applications, XML is used to store or transport data, while HTML is used to format and display the same data.

content.text: XML Separates Data from HTML
When displaying data in HTML, you should not have to edit the HTML file when the data changes.
content.html: When displaying data in HTML, you should not have to edit the HTML file when the data changes.

content.text: With XML, the data can be stored in separate XML files.
content.html: With XML, the data can be stored in separate XML files.

content.text: With a few lines of JavaScript code, you can read an XML file and update the data content of any HTML page.
content.html: With a few lines of JavaScript code, you can read an XML file and update the data content of any HTML page.

content.text: Transaction Data
Thousands of XML formats exist, in many different industries, to describe day-to-day data transactions:
content.html: Thousands of XML formats exist, in many different industries, to describe day-to-day data transactions:

content.text: Example: XML News
XMLNews is a specification for exchanging news and other information.
content.html: XMLNews is a specification for exchanging news and other information.

content.text: Using a standard makes it easier for both news producers and news consumers to produce, receive, and archive any kind of news information across different hardware, software, and programming languages.
content.html: Using a standard makes it easier for both news producers and news consumers to produce, receive, and archive any kind of news information across different hardware, software, and programming languages.

content.text: An example XMLNews document:

content.code:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<nitf>


<head>


<title>Colombia Earthquake</title>


</head>


<body>


<headline>


<hl1>143 Dead in Colombia Earthquake</hl1>


</headline>


<byline>


<bytag>By Jared Kotler, Associated Press Writer</bytag>


</byline>


<dateline>


<location>Bogota, Colombia</location>


<date>Monday January 25 1999 7:28 ET</date>


</dateline>


</body>

</nitf>
